rComments: I loved Elisa! I took her class in the summer and was sad that it ended so quickly. She's so quirky and intelligent and fun. She's really into video games and technology and introduced a lot of really cool digital content to all of us. She definitely expanded my appreciation of the genre. Especially loved her lectures on William Gibson.

Love the content, though I see how some might find it bland. Elisa seems so kind and accessible, and knows the topic well. She sets up workshops throughout the semester so you get some hands-on experience and apply some of the course content outside of class which I found creative and showed that she really cared about our experience and education.

Provides one-on-one instruction for the term project. Took it last year.  The content was not the most interesting one, but the way it was instructed was fairly interesting. Students were given opportunities to apply their knowledge to writing the course project. Exams were not difficult. The course didn't have a TA.

The course was difficult but for a good reason, as it was a foundation course; there was a lot material needed to be covered. However, it was possible to achieve a decent grade. Elisa, was quick with emails and made herself available to students whenever possible. Additionally, she expanded my understanding of and appreciation for bibliography.
